data.name: Dar-Tech Inc.
data.description: Dar-tech provides access to industry-respected manufacturers and formulators with high-quality, well-known specialty chemical products, an effective logistics network, and a responsive sales and customer service staff, all of whom deliver technical support with a customer-focused, personal approach.

data.name: Minex
data.description: MINEX® functional filler made from nepheline syenite is proven to offer superior color development, tint retention, and durability to a broad range of paints, coatings, adhesives, sealants, and inks. When added to paints and coatings, MINEX® provides unparalleled durability and resistance to abrasion, fading, cracking, and aging associated with both environmental and chemical exposures.

data.name: IMSIL
data.description: IMSIL® microcrystalline silica fillers are produced from an inert, naturally occurring alpha quartz with a unique grape-like morphology. Finer micronized grades are useful in formulating higher gloss paints and systems requiring controlled particle top size such as Industrial OEM topcoat coats and non-conductive inks. Intermediate size grades offer ideal and uniform gloss control for topcoats, coil coats and increased inter-coat adhesion between primers and topcoats. Coarser grades offer high solids loading with low viscosity,  texture, anti-skid  and abrasion resistance in industrial floor coatings and exterior deck coatings.

data.name: Dar-Tech Hauthane L-2183
data.description: Dar-Tech Hauthane L-2183 is an anionic, aliphatic, aqueous polyurethane dispersion. It is an adhesive grade polyurethane suggested for modifying industrial laminating adhesives. L-2183 may also be used in low tack pressure-sensitive applications. This grade can be used as supplied or blended with vinyl acetate/ethylene, styrene butadiene, and acrylic emulsions. The rheology of L-2183 may be modified with associative or acrylic thickeners for knife-over-roll or similar methods.

data.name: DEOX ECO 1
data.description: DEOX ECO 1 can be used as an interoperational fluid. It appears as a clear, colorless to straw-like liquid with a characteristic odor. It is soluble in water and has a pH of 10.8, a relative density of 1.051 kg/l, and a viscosity of 1.85 cSt at 40°C.

data.name: Dar-Tech Hauthane L-3972
data.description: Dar-Tech Hauthane L-3972 is a waterborne polyurethane. It is a resin used in the production of coatings and adhesives. Water-based polyurethane dispersions provide stain resistance in automotive interior plastic paints, lubricity in fly-fishing line coatings, durability in general aviation hangar floors, and crispness in sailcloth.

data.name: Securoc® B9
data.description: Securoc® B9 is produced from carefully selected, naturally occurring magnesium hydroxide. The standard quality of Securoc® B is guaranteed by means of an ISO 9001-certified quality management plan. The chemical composition of the raw material and the finished product is closely monitored, and particle size is kept within a narrow variation. Securoc® B products are developed as functional halogen-free flame retardant (HFFR) fillers for plastics and rubbers. Their flame retardant activity is primarily due to the endothermic decomposition of metal hydroxide (the heat sink effect) and the simultaneous release of water vapor. This reaction starts at about 300°C. Besides being flame retardant, they also possess a strong smoke-suppressing ability. These flame retardants are used in applications where processing temperatures exceed 200ºC, making ATH unsuitable. Its main uses are in wire and cable compounds, polyolefin roofing membranes, and electrical appliances based on thermoset compounds.

data.name: Access Rudolf Organosilane A311B
data.description: Access Rudolf Organosilane A311B is a highly effective adhesion promoter that enhances the bonding strength of polymers and inorganic substrates. It is a modified version of A311 and is specially designed for bonding applications that require high-temperature resistance. The product is a clear liquid and can be easily integrated into various formulations.

data.name: AFCONA 7466
data.description: AFCONA 7466 is a highly functional polymer containing carboxylic acids, providing excellent anti-settling, anti-floating, and anti-flooding properties. It also effectively stabilizes compounds containing color pigments and extenders, and, when combined with a suitable rheology agent, it can further enhance its anti-settling capabilities.

data.name: Ti-Pure™ R-931
data.description: Ti-Pure™ R-931 is a rutile titanium dioxide pigment designed to provide maximum hiding in high-quality, high-PVC architectural coatings. This product has maximized efficiency while maintaining the highest level of film integrity. It is manufactured by the chloride process and has at least 80% TiO2 content.

data.name: Cimpact® 610-610C
data.description: Cimpact® 610-610C is a high-brightness, high-purity, very platy, very fine talc that is recommended for excellent stiffness, HDT, and dimensional stability, as well as improved impact strength and esthetics in high-performance plastics, foamed plastics, and plastic films. It is available in compacted form (Cimpact® 610C) for maximum extruder throughput, minimum dust, and improved dispersion.

data.name: DeCAL 2031
data.description: DeCAL 2031 is a novel multifunctional acrylic dispersing agent based on new technology. The grade is an ideal problem-solving dispersant and is compatible with a wide range of organic and inorganic fillers and pigments utilized in water-borne systems. DeCAL 2031 is applicable in the coatings and adhesive industries but is also tailored to the agrochemical sectors, where it can be used as a stabilizer for concentrated emulsions, a dispersing agent for concentrated suspensions, and in the preparation of suspoemulsions.

data.name: AFCONA
data.seo_description: Knowde is the first marketplace for chemicals, polymers and ingredients. Our leading-edge digital capabilities connect thousands of sellers and buyers every day.

data.name: AFCONA 2590E
data.description: AFCONA 2590E is an effective defoamer for general industrial paints, wood coatings, and more. It can prevent the formation of foam and destroy existing foam under the surface, as well as reduce the chances of carters and fish eyes. It is a pre-emulsification water-based silicone defoamer, which can be easily incorporated into water-born coating systems.

data.name: AFCONA 3277P
data.description: AFCONA 3277P is an anti-crater, substrate wetting and leveling agent for powder coatings. It is a fluorocarbon modified polyacrylic in powder delivery form, designed specifically for powder coating. It can act as a non-silicone leveling agent to promote anti-cratering, leveling, and substrate wetting in powder coatings. It is recommended for all powder coating systems due to its polyacrylate structure, which is stable even at high temperatures during the curing process.

data.name: AFCONA 3581E
data.description: AFCONA 3581E is a silicone-based leveling and anti-crater agent for aqueous coatings that does not influence intercoat adhesion. AFCONA 3581E is the 52% effective substance version of AFCONA 3580, an organically modified polysiloxane with very short chain repeatable units of siloxane. These small molecules allow it to move very quickly to an area of defects. This offers very good anti-crater properties without causing intercoat adhesion problems.

data.name: AFCONA 3700P
data.description: AFCONA 3700P is a substrate wetting, leveling and flow control agent designed for powder coatings applications. AFCONA 3700P is a fluorocarbon modified polyacrylate in powder delivery form designed for powder coatings. It can serve as a non-silicone leveling agent to promote anti-crater, leveling and substrate wetting in powder coating systems.

data.name: AFCONA 5504S
data.description: AFCONA 5504S is a multi-functional additive that can help wet out difficult or contaminated substrates, lower the surface tension of the coating system, improve pigment grind efficiency, and prevent surface defects such as fisheyes, edge crawl, and craters. Furthermore, its great defoaming properties reduce water sensitivity of the final system due to its hydrophobic nature.

data.name: AFCONA 7375US
data.description: AFCONA 7375US is a modified fluorocarbon polyacrylate surface modifier with anti-foam and leveling properties. Higher fluorocarbon modification than AFCONA 7371. It is recommended for unsaturated polyester, PVC, epoxy, and polyurethane resin systems. With the higher fluorocarbon modification, AFCONA 7375US is excellent in surface tension related performance, such as anti- cratering, fiber wetting, pigment and extender wetting and faster leveling.

data.name: AFCONA 7510P
data.description: AFCONA 7510P is a block polymer with acidic functional groups and viscosity depressing properties in powder delivery form. It is recommended for use in unsaturated polyester, PVC, epoxy, and polyurethane resin systems. AFCONA 7510P is very similar to AFCONA 7500 and AFCONA 7520, but with a different modification. As a result, the performance of these three products is very close but may vary in different binder systems. Of the three products, AFCONA 7510P is the most hydrophilic.

data.name: AFCONA K172
data.description: AFCONA K172 is a wetting and dispersing additive designed to prevent flooding and sedimentation of pigments. It is a silicone-free version of AFCON K172 and can be used in the same applications. Additionally, AFCONA K172 can be post-added to resolve flooding and floating issues. When combined with a suitable high molecular weight dispersant, it can also act as a co-grinding agent.

data.name: AFCONA LE1000
data.description: AFCONA LE1000 is a solvent-free wetting and dispersing additive for universal colorants. It is an effective dispersing agent for the preparation of both solvent and water-based pigment concentrates. This high molecular weight dispersing agent stabilizes pigments through steric hindrance, making it suitable for all types of pigments.

data.name: AFCONA S713
data.description: AFCONA S713 is a wetting and dispersing additive used to prevent flooding and floating of pigments. It is very effective, offering performance close to that of a high molecular weight dispersant. It is recommended for medium to high polarity systems, such as polyurethane (PU), ultra-high-molecular-weight polyethylene (UHMWPE), ultraviolet (UV)-cured, nitrocellulose (NC), heat-cured, and acid-cured systems. This product is also widely used in printing inks.

data.name: AFCONA Aldehyde Resin SH-A81
data.description: AFCONA Aldehyde Resin SH-A81 is a very effective grind resin for solvent-based systems. Very good solubility and great compatibility in a wide range of solvent-based binders. Aldehyde resin is soluble in almost common paint solvents such as aromatic hydrocarbons, alcohols, ketones, esters and so on but insoluble in water. Its solubility in non-polar solvents such as mineral oil, aliphatic hydrocarbons, alicyclic hydrocarbons is limited.

data.name: AFCONA 1102
data.description: AFCONA 1102 is a universal dispersing resin designed for use in the preparation of universal pigment concentrates. It is a cheaper version of AFCONA 1101 and is compatible with most resin systems, such as polyurethane, alkyd melamine, acrylic melamine, polyester melamine (butylated and HMMM grade), and acid curing.

data.name: AFCONA 1103
data.description: AFCONA 1103 is a paint additive which is classified and labeled according to the CLP regulation. The product appears as a fluid with a characteristic odor. This product is registered under the Toxic Substances Control Act.

data.name: AFCONA 1501
data.description: AFCONA 1501 is a universal dispersing resin specifically designed for the preparation of universal pigment concentrates for water-based coatings. It provides good pigment wetting and stabilizing performance, as well as excellent compatibility with the resins commonly used in water-based coatings.

data.name: AFCONA 1503
data.description: AFCONA 1503 is a universal dispersing resin for preparation of VOC-free universal pigment concentrates for water based. It is a dispersing resin with self-emulsifying properties. AFCONA 1503 in combination with AFCONA 4560 has been developed to be considered suitable for the production of VOC-free pigment concentrates.

data.name: AFCONA 2018
data.description: AFCONA 2018 is a silicone-free defoamer that is recommended for systems where in-can transparency is important. It prevents the entrapment of air during processing steps such as stirring or pumping, and functions well during the application of paints and lacquers. AFCONA 2018 is well-suited for solvent-based wood finishes where foaming is a problem when applied by spraying.

data.name: AFCONA 2020
data.description: AFCONA 2020 is a very strong defoamer suitable for most solvent-based coatings, printing inks, and thermosetting resin systems. It eliminates foam and blistering, regardless of the source of the air bubbles. However, it is not suitable for transparent, high-gloss clear topcoats.

data.name: AFCONA 2021
data.description: AFCONA 2021 is a silicone-free defoamer with balanced performance for compatibility and defoaming, ideal for use in various coating systems. It can prevent air entrapment during stirring and pumping, and is especially suited for solvent-based coatings where foam formation is an issue when spraying or brushing.

data.name: AFCONA 2022
data.description: AFCONA 2022 is a strong defoamer that is easy to incorporate. This is a silicone-containing version of AFCONA 2020. This product prevents the formation of foam and blisters during the manufacturing and application of solvent-based and solvent-free coatings. AFCONA 2022 is a particularly compatible defoamer that works during production and application, especially in curtain coating processes.

data.name: AFCONA 2023
data.description: AFCONA 2023 is a moderate defoamer with minimal side effects. It prevents the formation of foam and blisters during the manufacturing and application of solvent-based coatings. The product has a moderate defoaming property and does not show many of the obvious side effects seen when using some stronger defoamers.

data.name: AFCONA 2024
data.description: AFCONA 2024 is a strong defoamer with leveling performance for all solvent-based coatings. It is a unique defoamer. It has very strong defoaming and anti-foam performances with additional good leveling. This is in contrary with most of the other defoamers, which influence the leveling performance negatively.

data.name: AFCONA 2025
data.description: AFCONA 2025 is a moderate defoamer with minimal side effects that prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application. It offers a combination of good defoaming and compatibility with most resin systems, and is recommended for medium-viscosity applications applied by spray and brush.

data.name: AFCONA 2027
data.description: AFCONA 2027 is a moderate defoamer with minimal side effects. AFCONA 2027 prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application. It offers a combination of good defoaming and compatibility with most resin systems. It is recommended for medium-viscosity applications applied by spray and brush.

data.name: AFCONA 2028
data.description: AFCONA 2028 is a moderate defoamer that is easy to incorporate. AFCONA 2028 prevents the formation of foam and blisters during the manufacturing and application of solvent-based wood finishes.AFCONA 2028 is particularly suitable as a defoamer for curtain coatings and may also be used during production. When foam causes a problem during packaging, AFCONA 2028 may be added slowly while stirring, which will speed up the bubble-breaking process. For this application, AFCONA 2028 is more user-friendly and easier to handle than AFCONA 2022 because it is less sensitive to crater formation and other well-known defoamer side effects.

data.name: AFCONA 2035
data.description: AFCONA 2035 is a moderate defoamer that minimizes side effects, prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application, and offers good defoaming and compatibility with most resin systems. It is recommended for medium-viscosity applications applied by brush and conventional spray methods, and is suitable for systems ranging from low to high polarity.

data.name: AFCONA 2036
data.description: AFCONA 2036 is a paint additive classified and labeled according to the CLP regulation, which replaces AFCONA 2035 in MIBK with DIBK. It prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application, and has a combination of good defoaming and compatibility with most resin systems. It is recommended for medium viscosity applications applied by spray and brush.

data.name: AFCONA 2038
data.description: AFCONA 2038 is a highly compatible defoamer that does not cause in-can haziness. It prevents the formation of foam and blisters during the manufacturing and application of solvent-based wood finishes. This defoamer has excellent compatibility properties, making it especially suitable for use in clear coatings and high gloss coatings. Additionally, it is suitable for use in applications where dry film transparency is essential, such as when applying thick clear coatings by conventional spraying.

data.name: AFCONA 2040
data.description: AFCONA 2040 is a moderate defoamer with minimal side effects that prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application. It offers a combination of good defoaming and compatibility with most resin systems. It is recommended for medium-viscosity applications applied by spray and brush, and is particularly suitable for systems ranging from low polarity to high polarity. AFCONA 2035 is recommended for brush and conventional spray applications.

data.name: AFCONA 2045
data.description: AFCONA 2045 is a silicone-based defoamer used to prevent the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application of solvent-based coatings, including polyurethane clear coats. It is effective even in difficult situations such as airless spray, brush, and roller application, and has strong defoaming properties with a very good transparent appearance.

data.name: AFCONA 2048
data.description: AFCONA 2048 is a defoamer for both spray and brush applications of solvent-based wood coatings. It is especially suited for high gloss solvent-based wood finishes and is highly compatible, not causing unacceptable haze. It is particularly useful for brush applications, as it quickly evaporates and provides rapid defoaming.

data.name: AFCONA 2050
data.description: AFCONA 2050 is a strong defoamer for most solvent-based coatings. AFCONA 2050 offers very strong defoaming and anti-foam performance with good compatibility in many resin systems. It is suitable for solvent-based coatings, printing inks and thermosetting resin systems. The product eliminates foam and blistering, regardless of whether the air bubbles are caused by the substrate.

data.name: AFCONA 2051
data.description: AFCONA 2051 is an effective defoamer with de-aeration properties. It prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application. The product offers a combination of compatibility with good defoaming and de-aeration properties, making it very suitable for clear coat applications.

data.name: AFCONA 2270
data.description: AFCONA 2270 is a moderate defoamer with minimal side effects that prevents the formation of foam and blisters during manufacturing and application. It offers good compatibility with most resin systems and is suitable for systems ranging from low to high polarity. It is recommended for medium-viscosity coatings applied using brush and conventional spray application.

data.name: AFCONA 2280
data.description: AFCONA 2280 is a very effective defoamer and air-releaser for solvent-based and solvent-less systems. AFCONA 2280 is a silicone-based product developed to produce rapid de-aeration for pigmented and mat finish of wood coating in NC, AC and PU. For high gloss and transparent wood coatings, it may cause some in can haziness when the dosage is higher than 0.50% in PU and AC system.

data.name: AFCONA 2290
data.description: AFCONA 2290 provides anti-foam and de-aeration properties for solvent-containing and solvent-free systems of epoxy, polyurethane, UPE and UV coatings. AFCONA 2290 contains a non-silicone defoaming substance which offers very good performance in both defoaming and anti-foaming. Due to its strong defoaming properties and silicone-free composition, it is also very suitable for primer coatings.

data.name: AFCONA 1101
data.description: AFCONA 1101 is a universal dispersing resin for preparation of universal pigment concentrate. AFCONA 1101 is designed to use as universal dispersing resin for the preparation of universal pigment concentrates. The stability and deflocculation ability of the pigment concentrate is highly depending on the selected dispersant. On the other hand, the compatibility of the pigment concentrate depends not only on the dispersant, but also on the universal resin chosen in the formulation.
